Sentencas: A unique requirement of underwater vehicles' power/energy systems is that they remain neutrally buoyant over the course of a mission.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system

Sentencas: Previous work published in the journal of Power Sources reported gross as opposed to neutrally-buoyant energy densities of an integrated solid oxide fuel cell/Rankinecycle based power system based on the exothermic reaction of aluminum with seawater.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system

Sentencas: This paper corrects this shortcoming by presenting a model for estimating system mass and using it to update the key findings of the original paper in the context of the neutral buoyancy requirement.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system

Sentencas: It also presents an expanded sensitivity analysis to illustrate the influence of various design and modeling assumptions.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system

Sentencas: While energy density is very sensitive to turbine efficiency (sensitivity coefficient in excess of 0.60), it is relatively insensitive to all other major design parameters (sensitivity coefficients < 0.15) like compressor efficiency, inlet water temperature, scaling methodology, etc.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system

Sentencas: The neutral buoyancy requirement introduces a significant ( similar to 15%) energy density penalty but overall the system still appears to offer factors of five to eight improvements in energy density (i.e., vehicle range/endurance) over present batterybased technologies.
Titulo: Estimating the neutrally buoyant energy density of a Rankine-cycle/fuel-cell underwater propulsion system
